data.description: Experience ease of living at 109 Branch Creek - a townhome that epitomizes quality and enjoys a superb location. Impeccably clean and meticulously maintained, this home exceeds expectations. The spacious garage is 1.5 car oversized, offering more than the usual size. Notable features include: 2 piece crown molding that adds a touch of elegance, ship lap on island and in family room, hardwood floors for a timeless look and easy maintenance, fresh paint, updated lighting, stainless steel appliances that bring a modern touch to the kitchen, backlit stone countertops on a island that is customized and extended, 42'' tall cabinets, roll out shelves for ease of storage. HVAC is only 2 years old and still under warranty. The front porch and back patio will be retreats for the outdoors.2 miles to Target, Home Depot, Lowes, Earth Fare  2.8 miles Harris Teeter 1 mile Downtown Summerville 5.8 miles to Summerville Medical (and speciality doctors)  6 miles to Trident Medical (and speciality doctors)  22 miles to Downtown Charleston   All furniture is for sale but must be on a bill of sale and negotiate price after ratification.
